1
00:01:22,220 --> 00:01:29,940
[Legend of Zang Hai]

2
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:32,900
[Episode 12]

3
00:01:35,310 --> 00:01:36,490
And I ran into an old face.

4
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,380
I know he came back

5
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:40,540
to kill Father and avenge his family.

6
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,290
[Late mother Shen's grave]
I told him to leave the Capital

7
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,540
and never come back.

8
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:46,540
Mother.

9
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,540
Did I do the right thing?

10
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,460
Zhinu, come and see.

11
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,690
It's a rare flower.

12
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:58,330
When fully grown,

13
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:00,020
its root and stem can be used in medicine,

14
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:02,930
while its flowers and seeds are poisonous.

15
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:10,850
Who is there?

16
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:16,380
Young Master.

17
00:02:17,590 --> 00:02:18,610
Why are you still here?

18
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:20,610
I still have pending businesses

19
00:02:21,150 --> 00:02:21,850
to attend to.

20
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,380
Not afraid I'll report you?

21
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:24,660
I was afraid.

22
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:26,820
That's why I came

23
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,500
to kill you today.

24
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:29,730
You...

25
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,660
But I've changed my mind.

26
00:02:34,030 --> 00:02:34,890
Listen.

27
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,290
I won't let you kill my father

28
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:37,660
just because you helped me.

29
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,010
You'd better give up.

30
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:43,340
What are you doing?

31
00:02:47,030 --> 00:02:48,500
Look, Young Master.

32
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:54,130
Is it the only flower growing on this grave?

33
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:57,610
What's so strange about flowers growing on the grave?

34
00:02:59,630 --> 00:03:00,980
Have you seen this flower

35
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,820
anywhere in the tomb?

36
00:03:06,630 --> 00:03:09,450
This is the "Solitary South Star." The whole plant is poisonous.

37
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,090
Why is this poisonous plant

38
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,780
only growing and flourishing

39
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,610
on your mother's grave?

40
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,860
Perhaps the wind carried the seeds

41
00:03:17,860 --> 00:03:18,890
from somewhere else.

42
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:23,010
It's a poisonous herb unique to Nanzhaozhou.

43
00:03:24,190 --> 00:03:25,610
The wind can't carry its seeds this far.

44
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:27,980
What are you implying?

45
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:31,680
Either someone planted it on your mother's grave

46
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:32,890
on purpose.

47
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:36,130
Or your mother's remains in the grave

48
00:03:36,590 --> 00:03:39,060
carry the seeds.

49
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:41,660
But I think you know

50
00:03:42,310 --> 00:03:44,130
that the former is hardly a possibility.

51
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,100
What are you implying?

52
00:03:47,710 --> 00:03:48,980
If I am right,

53
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:52,130
your mother died from this poison.

54
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,610
No way.

55
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:57,780
My mother died from illness.

56
00:03:58,030 --> 00:03:58,940
I never left her side

57
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,500
for a second before she died.

58
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:01,660
No one could have poisoned her.

59
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,010
The Solitary South Star

60
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:05,890
may not be as toxic as arsenic,

61
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:09,380
but with a little intake of its poison every day,

62
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:11,890
the toxin will accumulate in the organs over the years.

63
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:13,730
Eventually,

64
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:15,660
the victim dies.

65
00:04:17,390 --> 00:04:18,550
If you want the truth,

66
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:22,100
all you need to do is exhume your mother's remains

67
00:04:22,750 --> 00:04:23,900
from her grave.

68
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:28,540
You want me to dig up my mother's grave?

69
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:32,660
Don't you want to know the truth?

70
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,850
Perhaps the one who poisoned her

71
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:36,980
is the very person you revered

72
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,660
and trusted most.

73
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:42,580
Zang Hai, you're an animal!

74
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:43,850
What are you implying?

75
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,580
You're saying that my father killed my mother?

76
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,140
Nothing is impossible

77
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,170
in this world.

78
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,250
You want to dig up

79
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,020
my mother's grave and kill my father.

80
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:56,100
You fabricate lies to achieve your goal.

81
00:04:56,310 --> 00:04:57,660
You are insane!

82
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,490
Then tell me.

83
00:04:59,190 --> 00:05:00,810
Why are the Zhuang family's ancestors buried

84
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,170
in the southeast of the mausoleum

85
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,730
while your mother is buried on the north side alone

86
00:05:04,870 --> 00:05:06,020
with such a plain grave?

87
00:05:07,430 --> 00:05:10,050
Why haven't they moved her memorial tablet into the ancestral hall?

88
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:10,930
Shut up!

89
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:17,080
Most importantly,

90
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:19,100
Your mother's been gone for years.

91
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:22,370
Why has your father never once visited her grave?

92
00:05:24,140 --> 00:05:24,980
Why?

93
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:47,100
Ask someone you know.

94
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:50,530
See if this flower is poisonous like I said.

95
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,730
If you don't believe it is toxic,

96
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:18,170
do you dare to eat it?

97
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,780
I won't believe a word you said.

98
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:42,410
I'll give you one last chance.

99
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:44,490
Get out of my face!

100
00:06:46,310 --> 00:06:47,730
During tomorrow's ancestral rites,

101
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:50,340
open your eyes and see for yourself

102
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:53,980
whether I'm telling the truth.

103
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:25,540
Aim.

104
00:07:31,070 --> 00:07:32,900
Shoulders relaxed. Hands steady.

105
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:34,220
Exhale slowly.

106
00:07:35,510 --> 00:07:35,930
Shoot.

107
00:07:37,510 --> 00:07:38,340
I hit the bull's-eye.

108
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:40,140
Well done, Zhixing!

109
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,370
Have some water.

110
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:50,290
Mother, you promised

111
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,900
to make me tarts tonight if I hit the bull's-eye.

112
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:55,250
What a little foodie.

113
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,540
Won't you practice if I don't make you food?

114
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:01,020
This kid's got the same guts I had back in the day.

115
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,410
The next general in the family

116
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,340
will be him.

117
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,220
Make sure he practices riding and archery every day.

118
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:10,490
Don't let him slack off.

119
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,730
I can't lead troops like you.

120
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:14,610
How can I shoulder such a responsibility?

121
00:08:15,310 --> 00:08:16,540
Please teach him yourself.

122
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:17,930
Alright. Keep going.

123
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:49,060
My Lord, My Lady.

124
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:50,850
The carriages are ready.

125
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:53,610
The servants are already preparing

126
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,770
the incense and offerings at the mausoleum.

127
00:08:55,770 --> 00:08:57,550
[Marquis of Pingjin's Mansion]

128
00:08:57,550 --> 00:08:59,250
Have you brought all the hunting stuff?

129
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:00,220
Yes.

130
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:01,130
Rest assured, My Lady.

131
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:03,420
Father.

132
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:05,490
You got up early today.

133
00:09:05,870 --> 00:09:06,890
I dare not be late

134
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,100
for the ancestor veneration.

135
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:09,940
Good to know.

136
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:14,530
I don't see Mr. Zang today.

137
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:15,650
Isn't he coming?

138
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,610
He wasn't feeling well last night and asked for leave.

139
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:19,650
Let's set off.

140
00:09:21,630 --> 00:09:22,340
Anything else?

141
00:09:23,870 --> 00:09:24,250
I...

142
00:09:24,510 --> 00:09:25,180
Zhixing.

143
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:27,530
Let's not miss the hour for the ancestral rites.

144
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,460
- We can talk on the way... - Zhixing.

145
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:34,250
I have things to discuss with Father.

146
00:09:34,670 --> 00:09:36,730
Why don't you wait until we arrive?

147
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,700
Sandalwood's fragrance lingers,

148
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:05,060
pure and long.

149
00:10:05,630 --> 00:10:07,250
Steadying the state,

150
00:10:07,630 --> 00:10:09,250
our ancestors' virtue strong.

151
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:41,100
Jade cups hold fine wine,

152
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:43,130
like amber's glow.

153
00:10:43,390 --> 00:10:44,850
With cleansed hands we drink,

154
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,770
their grace to show.

155
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:13,220
My honored ancestors,

156
00:11:13,630 --> 00:11:15,580
your unworthy descendant Zhuang Luyin

157
00:11:15,870 --> 00:11:17,650
brought his family here to pay homage.

158
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:21,770
The family is thriving, my wife is virtuous, and my sons are filial.

159
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:25,250
May your noble spirits guard our way.

160
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:26,580
Pay respect.

161
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:30,940
Rise.

162
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,130
Pay respect again.

163
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,130
Rise.

164
00:11:39,750 --> 00:11:41,130
Pay respect again.

165
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:44,890
Rise.

166
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:49,220
Rites completed.

167
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:55,820
My Lord,

168
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:59,490
the offerings are blessed by the ancestors now.

169
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:00,820
Eating them brings good luck.

170
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:18,370
My Lord,

171
00:12:19,910 --> 00:12:21,940
these desserts have been left outside for a long time.

172
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:23,850
They must be covered in dust.

173
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:25,650
Let them make some new ones.

174
00:12:26,790 --> 00:12:29,130
Wrap the incense ash up and bury it at home.

175
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,700
It also brings good luck.

176
00:12:31,670 --> 00:12:32,580
Let's do as you say.

177
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:38,180
Where did this flower come from?

178
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:39,490
I have no idea.

179
00:12:40,910 --> 00:12:41,460
My Lady.

180
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,060
Is there anything wrong with this flower?

181
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:45,650
Don't ask so many questions.

182
00:12:46,510 --> 00:12:47,180
Throw it away.

183
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:47,850
Understood.

184
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:52,700
Father.

185
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:55,610
What now?

186
00:12:57,630 --> 00:12:59,180
You haven't visited my mother for so long.

187
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:01,180
You haven't visited her

188
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,730
ever since she passed away.

189
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:07,300
I'm going to the hunting ground later.

190
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:09,100
You don't like hunting, so go ahead

191
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,250
and visit your mother.

192
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:01,180
Zhifu.

193
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:02,700
See that?

194
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:07,180
I swear I'll get it today.

195
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:23,420
You two, go check.

196
00:14:23,510 --> 00:14:24,060
Father.

197
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:29,650
Nice shot.

198
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:30,850
Why are you here?

199
00:14:31,790 --> 00:14:32,980
I thought you didn't like hunting.

200
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,770
You taught me archery when I was a child.

201
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:38,010
I haven't forgotten it.

202
00:14:38,390 --> 00:14:40,770
You indulge in pleasure and never practice.

203
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,460
Come with us since you're here.

204
00:14:47,550 --> 00:14:48,010
Father.

205
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,770
I saw a little deer

206
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:54,180
heading in that direction.

207
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:55,650
I'll take a look.

208
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:56,770
Giddy yap.

209
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:06,700
Father.

210
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:08,850
What's wrong?

211
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:27,510
[Late mother Shen's grave]

212
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:28,460
What are you doing?

213
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,220
You won't come to see my mother.

214
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,130
I have no choice but to lure you here.

215
00:15:40,150 --> 00:15:41,610
Don't you miss her at all?

216
00:15:42,630 --> 00:15:43,610
Don't you want to see her?

217
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:47,250
You loved and cared for her so much.

218
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:49,060
Why have you changed?

219
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,820
Why has everything changed?

220
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:54,850
It pains me

221
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:57,770
to think about her.

222
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:02,460
So I'd rather not think about her

223
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:04,300
or visit her.

224
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:07,610
Do you still feel sad for her?

225
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:10,770
Enough.

226
00:16:11,550 --> 00:16:12,100
Let's go back.

227
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,010
Father, wait.

228
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,250
The flowers are blooming on Mother's grave.

229
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:22,490
Please take them back and keep them in the vase.

230
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:24,850
If she misses you,

231
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:28,130
perhaps she can see you through these flowers.

232
00:16:29,030 --> 00:16:29,650
I'm sure

233
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:32,220
she misses you a lot.

234
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:35,300
The talk of the spirits is all nonsense.

235
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:38,980
We martial arts practitioners don't believe that.

236
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:40,130
No matter what,

237
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:41,580
they bloomed on my mother's grave.

238
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:43,770
At least, bring them home for decoration.

239
00:16:53,870 --> 00:16:55,100
A real man shouldn't

240
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:57,530
be obsessed with flowers.

241
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:07,140
You missed your mother a lot today.

242
00:17:08,510 --> 00:17:10,380
I won't scold you for that.

243
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,090
It's getting late. Let's go.

244
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:28,900
[Late mother Shen's grave]

245
00:18:08,270 --> 00:18:09,980
You put the flowers there, didn't you?

246
00:18:12,790 --> 00:18:13,770
Speculation is groundless.

247
00:18:14,270 --> 00:18:16,140
It's better to see it with your own eyes.

248
00:18:47,030 --> 00:18:48,330
Your mother was buried outside

249
00:18:48,640 --> 00:18:49,530
of the mausoleum

250
00:18:50,070 --> 00:18:51,220
without an outer coffin.

251
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:54,490
That's why the coffin decayed so fast.

252
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:58,810
The status of the living ones is demonstrated

253
00:18:59,030 --> 00:19:01,330
through chariots, robes, and estates.

254
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:08,010
That of the deceased is shown through coffins, shrouds, and graves.

255
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:11,380
It's hard to imagine

256
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,380
that the Marquis's wife is buried like this.

257
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,140
I'm going to open it.

258
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:23,730
Wait for me up there

259
00:19:24,070 --> 00:19:25,290
if you can't bear to see it.

260
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:26,460
No need.

261
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,330
This is my mother.

262
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:35,660
Come on.

263
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:38,530
Three, two, one.

264
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:21,290
Your mother's wrist bones are deformed

265
00:20:21,790 --> 00:20:23,660
and obviously thinner than the ones

266
00:20:24,030 --> 00:20:25,140
of ordinary people.

267
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:28,380
The carpal bones of her left hand are also deformed.

268
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:30,460
Before she died,

269
00:20:30,830 --> 00:20:33,420
had she experienced weakness, dizziness, headaches,

270
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:35,140
and numbness in the limbs?

271
00:20:39,110 --> 00:20:42,140
At first, she was just dizzy and drowsy.

272
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:44,810
The physicians couldn't do much.

273
00:20:45,350 --> 00:20:48,250
Then things went worse and worse.

274
00:20:49,270 --> 00:20:52,220
She was dizzy, nauseous, and listless all day long.

275
00:20:53,310 --> 00:20:54,330
In the end,

276
00:20:56,790 --> 00:20:58,620
she was mumbling nonsense,

277
00:20:59,510 --> 00:21:01,730
having convulsion, and suffering unbearable pain.

278
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:04,980
That's right.

279
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:08,570
These symptoms point to Solitary South Star poisoning.

280
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:11,620
Those who are poisoned by that flower have something in common.

281
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:14,530
Their bones shrink and deform.

282
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:18,330
Besides, your mother was mumbling nonsense.

283
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:20,490
That's a sign of severe intoxication

284
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:22,530
as the poison affects the brain.

285
00:21:25,510 --> 00:21:26,420
